oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cheekwood
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Two views of Cheekwood showing the exterior of the mansion. The home, the walls, and foundation are made of limestone. The front of the home has Palladian-style windows, columns, a pediment. The west elevation, near the swan fountain, features a two-story, four bay loggia.

The Georgian revival-style mansion was built for Leslie and Mabel Cheek, the founders of the Maxwell House Coffee empire. The mansion and gardens, designed by New York residential and landscape architect Bryant Fleming, was finished in 1932. It now serves as a fine arts center and botanical gardens.
